Nurse Cristina Settembrese spends her days caring for COVID-19 patients in a hospital ward, and when she goes home, her personal isolation begins by her own choice.
The coronavirus brings with it forced isolation: Family members can't visit hospitalized patients.
Two months ago, the infectious disease ward where she works at San Paolo Hospital in Milan started treating only COVID-19 patients.
Suddenly, she had to learn how to operate machines she likens to “helmets” to help patients breathe.
